SIMPLE: spinner
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spinner
<hw>Spin"ner</hw> <pr>(sp⟦icr⟧n"n⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, spins one skilled in spinning;
a spinning machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A spider.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Long-legged
<xex>spinners</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A goatsucker; -- so called from
the peculiar noise it makes when darting through the air.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A spinneret.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ring spinner</b></col>, <cd>a machine for spinning, in
which the twist, given to the yarn by a revolving bobbin, is regulated
by the drag of a small metal loop which slides around a ring encircling
the bobbin, instead of by a throstle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spinneret</ent>⟦br⟧
